# Trivy ignore list — vulnerabilities accepted with justification.
# Format: one CVE/GHSA id per line, optional comment.
# Trivy reads this file from the working directory (repo root in our CI).
# Reviewed periodically when bumping container deps.

# litellm CVEs — transitive dep via fastmcp==3.2.* in mira-mcp.
# mira-mcp does NOT directly use litellm and does NOT expose the vulnerable
# litellm endpoints (/prompts/test, MCP stdio, data APIs).
# Upgrade blocked: litellm>=1.83.7 requires python-dotenv==1.0.1 which
# conflicts with fastmcp==3.2.0's python-dotenv>=1.1.0 requirement.
# Re-evaluate every fastmcp bump.

# CVE-2026-42203 / GHSA-xqmj-j6mv-4862 — LiteLLM SSTI in /prompts/test (HIGH)
GHSA-xqmj-j6mv-4862
CVE-2026-42203

# CVE-2026-42208 — LiteLLM Unauthorized data access and modification (CRITICAL)
CVE-2026-42208

# CVE-2026-42271 — LiteLLM Authenticated command execution via MCP stdio test
CVE-2026-42271

# CVE-2026-40217 — LiteLLM Arbitrary Code Execution via bytecode (HIGH)
# Present in litellm 1.83.0 (pulled in via openviking==0.3.9, the version
# we held back to). Fixed upstream in litellm 1.83.10, but litellm
# 1.83.7+ pins python-dotenv==1.0.1 which conflicts with fastmcp 3.x's
# python-dotenv>=1.1.0 — same chain documented above.
# mira-mcp does not call litellm directly and does not expose its
# vulnerable endpoints. Re-evaluate every openviking / fastmcp bump.
CVE-2026-40217
